# RESPONSIVE DESIGN DETAILS

Make the app behave like a real iPhone app.

Main mobile container:

* Max width: 390px
* Min height: 844px
* Center on desktop preview
* Full width on smaller screens
* Border radius if shown inside browser preview
* Use `height: 100dvh` where appropriate
* Use `padding-bottom` so bottom nav does not cover content

Breakpoints:

* For screens below 390px, reduce horizontal padding slightly
* For screens above 430px, keep app centered with max width
* Do not stretch content too wide on desktop

Use:

* `box-sizing: border-box`
* `overflow-y: auto`
* `position: sticky` or fixed bottom nav carefully
* `env(safe-area-inset-top)`
* `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`

Button sizes:

* Minimum tap target height: 44px
* Main buttons around 52px tall
* Rounded corners around 14px to 18px

Spacing:

* Screen horizontal padding: 20px to 24px
* Card padding: 16px to 20px
* Section spacing: 24px
* Avoid crowded rows

Typography:

* Main heading: 28px to 32px
* Section titles: 18px to 20px
* Body text: 14px to 16px
* Small labels: 12px to 13px

